<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Avil Page (Posts about youtube)</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" href="http://www.avilpage.com/tags/youtube.xml" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 22 Nov 2017 15:43:21 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Search, Play &amp; Download YouTube Videos From Command Line!</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/12/tech-search-play-download-youtube.html</link><dc:creator>Chillar Anand</dc:creator><description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;If You are using Linux,  You might be familiar with &lt;a href="http://rg3.github.io/youtube-dl/" target="_blank"&gt;youtube-dl&lt;/a&gt;, a small command-line program to download videos from &lt;a href="http://youtube.com/" target="_blank"&gt;YouTube&lt;/a&gt; and a few more sites. But You need to go to YouTube, grab the url and then give it to youtube-dl to download it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/np1/mps-youtube" target="_blank"&gt;mps-youtube&lt;/a&gt;, a terminal based YouTube player makes it possible to browse, play &amp;amp; download videos right from the terminal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can install it using pip  &lt;br&gt;&lt;pre style="border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgb(170, 204, 153); font-family: monospace, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.5279998779297px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; padding: 5px;"&gt;pip install mps-youtube&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;and start using in with&lt;br&gt;&lt;pre style="border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgb(170, 204, 153); font-family: monospace, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.5279998779297px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; padding: 5px;"&gt;mpsyt&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;It is better to set an alias for this&lt;br&gt;&lt;pre style="border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgb(170, 204, 153); font-family: monospace, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.5279998779297px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; padding: 5px;"&gt;alias yt="mpsyt"&lt;/pre&gt;By default it is configured to search music category and stream audio only. You can change it&lt;br&gt;&lt;pre style="border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgb(170, 204, 153); font-family: monospace, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.5279998779297px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; padding: 5px;"&gt;set music_search false&lt;br&gt;set show_video true&lt;/pre&gt;To get help, just press h.&lt;br&gt;To search for videos about Katy Perry, type /katy perry.&lt;br&gt;To stream a song, enter the number of the song and enter.&lt;br&gt;To download a video, type d &amp;lt;number&amp;gt; and it shows all the available formats, then you can select any video of your choice and download it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here are a few screenshots of it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-FyTu5R7uNeU/VH3NT3NboDI/AAAAAAAANZA/ICRbFAvwLEs/s1600/terminal-youtube1.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-FyTu5R7uNeU/VH3NT3NboDI/AAAAAAAANZA/ICRbFAvwLEs/s1600/terminal-youtube1.png" height="356" width="640"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-15RpL2mZyHk/VH3NUP6jEaI/AAAAAAAANZI/5RyepTegbAc/s1600/terminal-youtube2.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-15RpL2mZyHk/VH3NUP6jEaI/AAAAAAAANZI/5RyepTegbAc/s1600/terminal-youtube2.png" height="358" width="640"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-z38bcLKsjRo/VH3NT4dUrRI/AAAAAAAANZE/doElqCxTG4k/s1600/terminal-youtube3.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-z38bcLKsjRo/VH3NT4dUrRI/AAAAAAAANZE/doElqCxTG4k/s1600/terminal-youtube3.png" height="358" width="640"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>cli</category><category>mps-youtube</category><category>tech</category><category>terminal</category><category>youtube</category><category>youtube-dl</category><guid>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/12/tech-search-play-download-youtube.html</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Dec 2014 14:34:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>

    </title><link>http://www.avilpage.com/2013/11/avil-page-watch-youtube-videos-without-buffering-slow-internet-connection.html</link><dc:creator>Chillar Anand</dc:creator><description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;
    So, You have a slow internet connection and You want to watch your favorite videos without buffering? Here is the trick. One thing you can do immediately
    increase buffering speed is to reduce the quality of the video.&lt;br&gt;
    &lt;br&gt;
    The other thing you can do is to reduce the information on the page other than video. To do this, you can go to the bottom of the page and click on " Try
    something new "  In the next page you will find " Youtube feather " If you opt in for the Youtube feather, you can watch videos without buffering even
    with a slow internet connection. However the comments under the video and some other features will be missing!&lt;br&gt;
    &lt;br&gt;
    Watch the video to know how to do that!&lt;br&gt;
